Ateliere Deschise de Sculptura - Sculpture Open Studios

Bucharest, 15/16 - 22/23 Oct

Cultural event that offers free access in the studios of the most appreciated romanians contemporary sculptors it's dedicated to the Bucharest public in October for two consecutive weekends: 15 - 16, 22 - 23 and for organized groups in the period between 17 to 21 October. At this event edition the main area where the studios are located is Combinatul Fondului Plastic plus a few sculptors studios located in ​​Charles de Gaulle and Piata Romana area. The schedule is: Saturday 10am - 19pm on and Saturday 10am-17pm. You are invited to visit the studios of the sculptors: Adrian Pirvu, Alin Florin Carpen,Ana Zoe Pop, Anton Ratiu, Vlad Aurel, Catalin Geana, Cristian Pentelescu, Doru Nicolae Dragusin,Dumitru Pasima, Giani Iosif Amarandei, Ioan Medrut, Laurentiu Mogosanu, Marian Zidaru, Mircea Roman, Titi Ceara, Valentin Duicu, Victoria Zidaru.

Evenimentul cultural ce ofera accesul liber in atelierele unora dintre cei mai importanti sculptori contemporani romani va fi rezervat publicului bucurestean,in luna octombrie, timp de doua weekenduri consecutive, 15-16 si 22-23 octombrie, si grupurilor organizate, in perioada dintre acestea, 17-21 octombrie. In editia acestui sfarsit de an, zona principala o va constitui Combinatul Fondului Plastic, fieful atelierelor de sculptura din Bucuresti, la care se adauga ateliere din zona Pietei Charles de Gaulle si Piata Romana.

Antony Gormley: CAST

13 May 2016 - 30 Jul 2016

An exhibition of new prints by Antony Gormley, one of Britain’s most widely acclaimed artists, will be unveiled from 13 May - 30 July 2016. Marking his first project and exhibition with the Alan Cristea Gallery, Antony Gormley has made a series of works that consider how our physical freedom and imaginative potential is increasingly conditioned by the built environment.

Agustina Woodgate, '$8.05 (Ink on paper diptych )', 2016, Spinello Projects | Artsy

Agustina Woodgate creates art across multiple disciplines, her primary focus being the interplay between human beings and their surroundings. Born in Buenos Aires, Woodgate moved to Miami in 2004, where she gained recognition for covertly stitching labels inscribed with poems into thrift-store clothing ("poetry bombing,") and for her work made with human hair.
PuzzledDAD series (2), 2015 Acrylic, oil and ink on linen 36 x 48 inches (91.4 x 121.9 cm)

Less is More

Londonian photographer Rankin - Leica S - Kunsthalle Rostock

With Less is More you are currently presenting an exhibition of your work at the Kunsthalle Rostock in Germany. The exhibit features early imagery from your time as a co-founder of Dazed & Confused all the way through to your more experimental contemporary work.

Less is More - by wordisiac

Minimalism in visual art, generally referred to as "minimal art", "literalist art" and "ABC Art" emerged in New York in the early 1960s as new and older artists moved toward geometric abstraction; exploring via painting in the cases of Frank Stella, Kenneth Noland, Al Held, Ellsworth Kelly, Robert Ryman and others; and sculpture in the works of various artists including David Smith, Anthony Caro, Tony Smith, Sol LeWitt, Carl Andre, Dan Flavin, Donald Judd and others.
